        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer7943770" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17680655718685815421">The world that we know will not remain for very long if current trends continue. This book is the perfect antidote to claims that we are about to over-populate the planet. In fact, European countries have negative birth rates and the next fifty years could see major changes in their demographics. The massive immigrant populations from Muslim countries could quite plausibly overrun some of the nations of Europe within the next half-century. Steyn presents his evidence, his arguments and the inevi</span>
  <span id="freeText17680655718685815421" style="display:none">The world that we know will not remain for very long if current trends continue. This book is the perfect antidote to claims that we are about to over-populate the planet. In fact, European countries have negative birth rates and the next fifty years could see major changes in their demographics. The massive immigrant populations from Muslim countries could quite plausibly overrun some of the nations of Europe within the next half-century. Steyn presents his evidence, his arguments and the inevitable conclusions if his evidences are correct in so witty a manner that his reading is truly delightful. There is nothing so diverting as the prose of a well-read author with a good wit, as is Mr. Steyn. </span>
