  <span id="freeText1104400273103027867" style="display:none">I've read Steyn online, in commentaries, and magazines, but never attempted a book by him. Shame on me! The guy is a delight, and incendiary to boot. How I knew I would like this book before I even cracked it: the cover quote. Usually these things are drippy and praise-laden, along the lines of "Smith's book is a masterpiece of zippity do dah". <br />What does this guy put on the cover? <br />"The arrogance of Mark Steyn knows no bounds" - Prince Turki al-Faisal<br />Heh.<br />This is a guy who can write seriously and urgently about complex and interesting subjects, but isn't so weighted with self-importance that he can't look into the camera and wink. Which he does. Often. <br />I may have found a new boyfriend here. </span>
